# CODEOWNERS — the human-absolute gate.
#
# A green build is NECESSARY BUT NEVER SUFFICIENT for the surfaces below. They encode the
# product's judgment and trust: a subtly-wrong DEFINITION of risk is the one bug that discredits
# the whole tool, and only a human catches it. An agent may propose; a maintainer ratifies.
#
# Team handle is a placeholder until the org team exists.

# The action-risk vocabulary and standards crosswalk — reviewed data, not code.
/packages/vocabulary/                 @formael/actlint-maintainers

# The labeled eval corpus and scorer — the quality number.
/eval/                                @formael/actlint-maintainers

# Trust surfaces.
/SECURITY.md                          @formael/actlint-maintainers

# The supply-chain surface — CI, release, and provenance. A workflow edit is a supply-chain event.
/.github/workflows/                   @formael/actlint-maintainers
/.github/dependabot.yml               @formael/actlint-maintainers
/.changeset/config.json               @formael/actlint-maintainers
